General Information
===================

paxman is a multi-platform game. It has been modeled on Pacman, which
was developed by Namco in Japan, 1980.

paxman is free software. The licensing terms for paxman, the GNU LGPL,
allow it to be used by all developers, including those developing
proprietary software, without any license fees or royalties.

The official web site is:
  http://pacman.sourceforge.net/

Installation
============

See the file 'INSTALL'

Release notes
=============

See the file 'ChangeLog'

How to report bugs
==================

Bugs should be reported to one of the authors.
See the file 'AUTHORS'

In the bug report please include:
  
* Information about your system. For instance:

   - What operating system and version
   - What version of X
   - For Linux, what version of the C library

* How to reproduce the bug. 

  Please tell us how to reproduce the bug. Otherwise, please add the
  source code of a short test program that exhibits the behavior.

* If the bug was a crash, the exact text that was printed out when the
  crash occured.

* Anything else you think is relevant.

Patches
=======

Patches should also be submitted to one of the authors (See the file
'AUTHORS'). If the patch fixes an existing bugm, add the patch as an
attachment to that bug report. 

Otherwise, send us a new bug report that describes the patch, and
attach the patch to that bug report.

